# SHA-256 integrity manifest for raw source archives.
#
# This file is POPULATED BY `make data` on first successful download and
# committed thereafter, so that any subsequent clone can verify byte-for-byte
# that it holds the same source data as the analysis was run against.
#
# Format:  <sha256>  <path relative to repository root>
#
# Expected entries once populated:
#   data/raw/tri_2019/2017-05-12_batchdata_updated_struct_errorcorrect.mat
#   data/raw/tri_2019/2017-06-30_batchdata_updated_struct_errorcorrect.mat
#   data/raw/tri_2019/2018-04-12_batchdata_updated_struct_errorcorrect.mat
#   data/raw/tri_2020/<closed-loop batch files>
#   data/raw/nasa_pcoe/5.+Battery+Data+Set.zip
#   data/raw/calce/CS2_*.zip, CX2_*.zip
#   data/raw/oxford/Oxford_Battery_Degradation_Dataset_1.mat
